President Muhammadu Buhari has said that Nigeria has moved a step closer to its quest of full utilisation of the nation’s abundant gas potentials.  Speaking Tuesday at the launch of the Integrated Gas Handling Facility and LPG Processing and Dispensing Plants in Oredo, Edo State, President Buhari noted that the Oredo Integrated Gas Handling Facility will deliver two hundred and forty thousand metric tons of commercial grade Liquefied Petroleum Gas and Propane to the domestic market as well as create hundreds of direct and indirect employment opportunities for youths.  Earlier in his remarks, the Minister of State for Petroleum Resources, Timipre Sylva, described the project as part NNPC’s desire to end gas flares while increasing Nigeria’s value realisation from gas.  Similarly, the Group Managing Director, Nigerian National Petroleum Corporation NNPC Mele Kyari while calling on the Oba and people of OLOGBO, EDO State to see the project as their own also advised that the presence of peace in the community will create a conducive environment for businesses to thrive.